<h2> Definition </h2>

<h3> Asking for an explanation </h3>

When asking for an explanation, the speaker ends the sentence with <strong>@HI{{ndesuka}}</strong>.
This form is used
when the speaker:
<ol>
<li> guesses a reason or cause for what has been heard and confirms to see if this is correct
<li> asks for information about what has been seen or heard
<li> asks the listener to explain the reason or cause of what has been seen or heard
</ol>

<h3> Offering an explanation </h3>

When the speaker wishes to offer an explanation, he ends the sentence with <strong>@HI{{ndesu}}</strong>.
This form is used
when the speaker:

<ol>
<li> has been asked for an explanation (which the listener does by using one of the forms above) and wishes
to state a reason or cause in the reply
<li> wishes to add a reason or cause to what he has stated
</ol>

<h3> Introducing a topic </h3>

<strong>@HI{{ndesuga}}</strong> is used to introduce a topic.
It is often followed by a request, an invitation or an
expression seeking permission. However, the trailing clause can be omitted.

